description:
9Lives is a rapidly expanding veterinary group with multiple veterinary offices, ranging from GP to ER. We started as a feline only practice and have expanded to provide 24/7 ER.  All hospitals are fully equipped with digital radiography, ultrasound, in house blood machines, etc. We have a brand-new CT scan in our 24-hour facility, and we will be offering ambulance service to help our patients transfer between locations as needed. Our nursing staff is fully bilingual and can assist with all of your translation needs.  We are committed to providing continuing education and learning opportunities abound.

 Job Highlights

Experience in handling animals;
Shift duty is required;
Fringe benefits, medical insurance, commission scheme, 13-month salary

 Veterinary Nurses

 Job Description

Support animal handling during consultations, examinations, testing, X-ray and surgeries, as assigned;
Dispense medication as instructed by veterinary doctors and explain dosage and precautions to customers;
Look after hospitalized animals, which include cleaning, feeding and etc;
Act as translators between clients and veterinary staff (English and Cantonese) during consultation;
Manage customers services, such as registrations, billing and etc.
Support inventory control, record of movements and ordering; Perform regular stocktake and check expiry dates; 
Perform any other duties, as assigned.

 Requirements

Excellent spoken English and Cantonese and good interpersonal skills;
Passionate in animal welfare;
Candidates with AIRC Certificate at Grade 2 / Grade 4 is an advantage;
Shift duty is required, including Saturday, Sunday and public holidays
Immediate available is preferred;

 Offer

- Our salary package commensurate with experience and qualifications;

- Fringe benefits included medical Insurance, commission scheme, overtime compensation, 13-month salary and staff discount.

Responsibilities

Synthesis & Quality Control of Radiopharmaceuticals in Cleanroom Environment using Medical Cyclotron;
Perform daily routine task along with general lab cleaning;
Performs clerical and administrative tasks, including maintenance of daily production records, report preparation and maintenance records;
Requirement

Degree or Higher Diploma in Analytical Science/Applied Chemistry or other related disciplines;
Familiar with pharmaceutical analysis in GC, HPLC and TLC 
Knowledge of cGMP/ISO and working experience in relevant position will be an advantage;
Strong documentation practices, oral communication, and writing skills
Proficiency in reading, writing and comprehension skill of English & Chinese;
Proficiency in MS Office applications;
Shift duty is required
Candidate with less experience will be considered as technician.
Contact us

Qualified candidate, please email your full resume with academic credentials, working experience, expected salary and availability by clicking the "apply now" button as below.

Job Duties:

Perform ultrasound examinations, provide and maintain professional services;
Prepare preliminary diagnostics reports, provide extensive client care;
Job Requirements:

Degree holder of Radiography or equivalent;
Minimum 2 years of solid experiences;
Customer-oriented with good command of spoken and written English and Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);
Maintain a high level of accuracy and professional manner
Fixed rest days on Sundays and public holidays, NO night-shift is required

Interested parties please send full resume with available date, current & expected salary to Human Resources Department by "Apply Now".

Job Responsibilities

Responsible for day to day chemical analysis of raw/in-process materials and finished products;
Prepare / review of test result;
Assist in development, modification and validation of testing method;
Conduct calibration and routine maintenance of laboratory instrumentation;
Assist in generation and review of laboratory documents; &
Implement requirements of GMP in daily operation.

Job Requirements

Degree or above in Chemistry, Chinese Medicine, Analytical Science or related discipline;
Minimum 1 year hands on experience chemical testing preferably in pharmaceutical, herbal material or food testing;
Knowledge on method development and validations will have additional advantage;
Familiar with instrumental analysis including GC-FID and HPLC;
Experience with GMP and ISO 17025 is preferred but not essential;
Self-initiative and a good team player;
Proficient in written/spoken English and Chinese;
Proficient in Microsoft Office; &
Candidate with less relevant experience or lower qualification will be considered as Assistant Quality Control Chemist.

How to Apply

You are invited to send in your application and CV stating the position you are applying for together with your current and expected salary, either by Clicking "Apply Now" or Mail to 12-14 Dai Wang Street, Tai Po Industrial Estate, Tai Po, NT. 

Europharm Laboratoires (Hong Kong) Company Limited is an equal opportunities employer. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used only for consideration of application for relevant/similar post(s).  All personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months.

We are BNS Medical Imaging Centre Ltd. To cope with our rapidly expansion, we are looking for high caliber candidate to join our team.

 Job Description

l  Registered Radiographer of Hong Kong with valid Annual Practicing Certificate and Irradiating Apparatus License;

l  Experience in MRI / CT / Ultrasound / Mammogram is preferred;

l  Ability to perform a comprehensive range of radiographic procedures;

l  Good command of spoken English and Chinese;

l  Ability to provide high quality patient service.

l  Experienced candidates are highly preferred

l  Immediately available is highly preferred

All applications applied through our system will be delivered directly to the advertiser and privacy of personal data of the applicant will be ensured with security.

Responsibilities:

To handle quality control matters of the factory;
Quality inspection of sampling and testing;
To responsible for line clearance and routine inspection for production process;
To conduct calibrations for programs, monitor and factory equipment;
To check the quality of raw materials, packaging materials and finished products to ensure compliance with standards;
To associate documentation system such as standard operating procedures and wide variety of specifications;
Prepare and complete QC and quality assurance reports;
Assist in the company research & development projects;
To identify and correct on-going quality problem and arrange suitable external testing services
To perform any ad-hoc quality duties as assigned.

Requirements:

Degree or above in Chinese Medicine, Pharmaceutical, Food Science or related discipline; or Higher diploma with strong QC experience in pharmacy or Chinese medicine fields;
At least 5 years or above working experience in the quality control, preferably in Chinese medicine or Western medicine;
Good interpersonal skills;
Self-motivated and a team player;
Good usage experience of pharmaceutical testing equipment will be an advantage, such as disintegration tester and moisture balance etc.;
Candidates with more experience or knowledge will be considered as “Quality Control Supervisor”.

We offer a competitive remuneration package including excellent career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send us an email or contact to WhatsApp 6433 5952.

All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.
